content.description:
Mantle onto the obvious rail and lunge for the lip far above. Slide back down to the rail and try again...

Probably easier for taller folks.
content.location: On the east side of the boulder, just right of Insanity Later.

content.description:
From a low crouch, power up to the technical dihedral, doing insecure moves on sometimes imaginary features. The dihedral leads to a huge angular brick-like hold at the ~15 foot level. Use this hold, as well as some sketchy feet, to power up to the good hold up and left, and hold it together for the rock-over. A proud v4.

Alternate start at the left on the start jugs for Chemical Imbalance traversing into the seam goes at about the same grade.
content.location: The obvious dihedral on the south face of the Camp Serene boulder.

content.description:
Start low on Serenity Now, work up into the dihedral, but cut right onto the odd fin-like feature, and transition into the awesome slightly overhanging face to the right. Finish with (hopefully) control up a number of slopers, and do a not-insignificant rock-over to finish. The crux is the transition onto the fin from Serenity Now.

As great as Serenity Now, but it is a little steeper, longer, and requires sloper-pawing to the finish. Another proud problem.
Climb the arete to the right of Ryan's Problem and Serenity now. Finish via a sloping hold at the lip.

A great and stout problem for the grade. Mantel onto the jugs and use some insecure smears to lieback into the upper section of the crack. Pretty heady finish! Bring pads. Crux is low but not easy at the top.
content.protection: Depends on confidence but at least 3 if this climb is near your limit.
content.location: Front side of the boulder facing the highway. The obvious crack feature.

content.description:
The downclimb on the east side of the boulder. A dihedral, cracky, blocky line with a tree near the bottom.

May need a cleaning from time to time for a safe descent. Very mossy!
content.protection: Pad if you want. Very secure but tall.

content.description: Start on the obvious jugs down low, and climb straight up the arete.
content.location: The arete to the right of the Camp Serene Face.
